Status Update - Halloween Edition (Apparently?)
来源：Sponge Community  作者：DarkArcana（不是Dark_Ark）
Phew, it’s been a very busy week, we’ve been doing a heap of work across all aspects of Sponge, check it out below:呼，这周可真忙。在这周中，我们完成了涉及Sponge几乎全部领域的大量工作，来看看吧：
General UpdateAs you may already know, our two initial releases of Sponge will be for Forge and later for Glowstone. We were hoping to release the Sponge for Forge version earlier, but recent events (Microsoft’s acquisition of Mojang, the departure of one of Forge’s lead developers, the great number of changes in MC 1.8) had delayed the progress of Forge significantly. The good news, however, is that it looks like Forge for Minecraft 1.8 may be ready in the near future, which means we’ll be able to start making plans to publish our first release very soon. We still plan on releasing the API this month.
Normally, the process for a modification of Mojang’s code involves three steps:
The first step involves undoing some of the work that Mojang does to make it difficult to create a moddable code base. This process is usually called “mapping” or “deobfuscation.”After this process, Mojang’s code looks like something readable, the modifications that were made in the prior version of MC must be re-applied which is not always as straightforward as you may think. Mojang makes changes to their code (entire paragraphs are removed or added, as an analogy). This step is called “re-applying patches.”After re-applying patches, the last part is to find and fix bugs. Trying to re-apply patches is a tiresome process because it involves hundreds of changes in hundreds of places.
Forge depends on the MCP project, which handles the first step - mapping. They finished a few weeks ago, and they do a very good job very quickly, and have been doing it consistently since 2010.
Right now, we’re waiting on Forge to finish the second step. As previously mentioned, the recent events have caused some delays. Minecraft 1.8 brought about many tweaks to how things are done in the code, and we’re pleased that they managed to get Forge out in such a timely manner.
Once we get the ball rolling with 1.8, we plan to look into what we can do to make sure that the 1.9 release of Sponge is much quicker, even if it involves relying less on Forge for the first few releases.
综合情况：

你或许已经知道了，Sponge的第1、2个版本将支持Forge，对于Glowstone的支持将会在那之后放出。我们十分希望Forge版本的Sponge能够早日发布，但是最近的事情（微软收购Mojang、Forge领头开发者的离开和Minecraft1.8大量的新功能）将Forge的开发延缓地很厉害。当然，好消息是，Minecraft1.8的Forge可能将在近期发布，这就意味着我们马上就可以动手计划我们的第一个服务端版本了。我们仍旧计划在这个月（11月）内发布API。

一般来说，对于Mojang的代码的处理过程包括如下三个步骤：
第一部是去除Mojang所做的为搭建MOD平台增加难度的一些东西。这个过程一般叫做“反混淆”在反混淆之后，Mojang的代码终于可以阅读了，在上一个版本制作的对于源代码的修改并不能直接应用在新版本的代码上，要知道，Mojang也会更改他们的代码（比如说有的时候整段代码会被加入、去除）。这一部叫做重新应用补丁。在重新应用补丁之后，最后一步是找到并且修补BUG。重新应用补丁是一个很累人的工作，因为它涉及到数百处修改。

Forge依赖于MCP（MinecraftCoderPack），MCP负责三个步骤中的第一步 — 反混淆。他们在几周之前完成了自己的工作，并且完成的既快速、又漂亮。值得一提的是他们自从2010年就开始制作MCP了。

现在我们正在等待Forge来完成以上三个步骤中的第二部。正如之前所提到的，最近的一些时间造成了很大的延迟。Minecraft 1.8中包含了许多改变，对于Forge能够如此快的完成工作，我们也感觉很高兴。

只要我们能够顺利完成1.8的工作，我们将会持续计划之后的事情，1.9版本的Sponge将会更快，甚至可能在前几个版本中不那么依赖Forge。

Development
Sponge’s development is coming along nicely. We have chosen Zidane to lead the development team.
Developer applications are currently being examined by Zidane and Dark-Arcana. If you’re wondering about the result of your developer application, then be aware that they have many applications to review and are reaching out to those who had applied. If you have not received a response yet, please be patient.
As we accept individuals to help with development, we assign them to certain areas of the API, preferring to make those who are experienced with that type of API to be responsible for it. We will be publishing these assignments once we’ve figured it out.
Remember that if you are interested in helping out with development, you can follow and add code to ourGitHub repository, or apply for a developer position.
开发
Sponge的开发目前十分顺畅。我们选择了Zidane来领导开发工作。开发申请目前由Zidane和Dark-Arcana处理。如果你想知道你的申请的结果，请知会目前有太多开发者申请开发Sponge以至于他们有些忙不过来。所以如果你没有收到答复，请耐心。
我们接受个体开发者参与开发，并且我们将会给他们安排API中的某些功能，在API安排上，我们会比较偏向那些有着开发同种API经验的人。我们将会在整理完之后将这些明确的分工发布出来。
如果你对于帮助我们的开发有兴趣的话，你可以关注或者为我们的Github上的代码添砖加瓦，你也可以申请开发Sponge

Changes in Sponge Staff
When we started Sponge, we gathered pretty much everyone around the community that we could find and stuffed them into one group. This made communication easy, but it made organizing our efforts a lot harder as some people who had joined early on weren't able to commit enough free time. To help rectify this, we've been restructuring the Sponge team internally and contacting people individually to see who would be able to contribute at this time. However, this means that the core team and staff lists are a little smaller. Don’t worry - we’re still and always will be looking for more help when we need it. We understand that people have other commitments to attend to, and simply can’t devote all of their time on the Sponge Project.
Sponge管理人员的变化
当我们开启Sponge企划的时候，我们几乎找到了我们所能找到的所有人并且将它们硬生生的塞进了一个组里。诚然，这让交流变得很简单，但这个样子让我们的组织变得很难。为了帮助解决这个，我们在内部改变了团队的联系方式，我们将采用私下的方式来联系某个开发者是否有时间。但是，这代表着我们的核心团队和管理人员列表将会更小。别担心 - 我们一直在这里，如果我们需要更多帮助的话，我们会开口的。我们知道大部分开发者都有自己的其他事情，我们也不可能强求他们把自己的所有时间都花在开发Sponge上。
